First Lady Jill Biden will be joined by selected guests in the viewing box for President Biden's State of the Union Address. These guests were chosen because they represent policies or themes to be addressed by the President in his speech. The guests include Joseph "JoJo" Burgess, a United Steelworkers Local 1557 trainer; Joshua Davis, a 7th-grade diabetes advocate; Refynd Duro, a Progressive Care Unit Nurse; Patrick "Pat" Gelsinger, the CEO of Intel; Frances Haugen, a former Facebook lead product manager on Civic Misinformation; Melissa Isaac, a protector of the young and founder of Saginaw Chippewa Indian Tribe's Project AWARE Program; Danielle Robinson, the surviving spouse of Sergeant First Class Heath Robinson; and Kezia Rodriguez, a student-parent at Bergen Community College. The Second Gentleman, Mr. Douglas Emhoff, the President's sister, Valerie Biden Owens, and the Ambassador of Ukraine to the United States, Oksana Markarova, will also join the First Lady in the viewing box.